The paper proposes a method for performing information bottleneck in more general domains, which involves using a non-parametric estimator of mutual information and a variational approximation. The method is implemented using neural networks and gradient-based optimization, which suggests that it falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information theory concepts such as mutual information, which suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper applies the method to image data (MNIST dataset), which suggests that it could also belong to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) categories.
